<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-09-01.1.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0901.htm">Scottish Executive</major-heading>

<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-09-01.2.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0901.htm#1">Airports</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-09-01.2.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80056" speakername="Rosie Kane (Glasgow) (SSP)" spid="S2W-27651" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0901.htm#1" holdingdate="2006-08-30">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether concerns expressed by Prestwick Airport&rsquo;s air traffic controllers&rsquo; trade union in respect of the dangerous nature of the United States of America&rsquo;s munitions supply flights have been conveyed to it and, if so, whether it has made representations to UK Ministers to outline these concerns.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-09-01.2.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80109" speakername="Tavish Scott" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0901.htm#1">

  <p>The Scottish Executive has not received representations from Glasgow Prestwick Airport&rsquo;s air traffic controllers&rsquo; trade union on this issue.</p>

</reply>


